NAME
    standard_deviation - calculate the standard deviation of a sample 
 
SYNOPSIS
    #include <acme.h>
    static inherit AcmeStat;
    #include AcmeStatInc
 
    float standard_deviation( float *sample );
 
DESCRIPTION
    Returns the standard deviation of a sample.  This is actually
    just the square root of the variance.
 
EXAMPLE
    standard_deviation( ({ 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 }) ) -> 1.58114
 
SEE_ALSO
    deviation(A), variance(A)
 
LAST MODIFIED                               
    980502 Devo
